      "Text": "haproxy security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for haproxy is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "HAProxy is a free, very fast and reliable solution offering high availability, load balancing, and proxying for TCP and HTTP-based applications. It is particularly suited for very high traffic web sites and powers quite a number of the world\u0026apos;s most visited ones.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nAn issue was discovered in HAProxy before 3.3.6. The HTTP/3 parser does not check that the received body length matches a previously announced content-length when the stream is closed via a frame with an empty payload. This can cause desynchronization issues with the backend server and could be used for request smuggling. The earliest affected version is 2.6.(CVE-2026-33555)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for haproxy is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "haproxy",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
